    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-11T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-11T13:00:00-05:00" n="700"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/410</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-11T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 12, 2.10 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>987. Department’s 818, January 8, 7 p.m. Embassy firmly of opinion, in which
                    Major <persName>Belmont</persName> concurs, that for any licenses for <pb
                        facs="0825" n="1659" xml:id="pg_1659"/> embargoed articles to be issued by
                    War Trade Board would be fatal to pending negotiations. That Spain has been able
                    until the last few days to secure export permits for all she desired from the
                    United States notwithstanding embargo, has created feeling here that our embargo
                    was not real. Spain is just beginning to appreciate her position and the need of
                    coming to terms with us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
